{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":738,"text":"I haven't told many people this,"},{"time":2436,"text":"but in my head, I've got"},{"time":4832,"text":"thousands of secret worlds all going on"},{"time":6969,"text":"all at the same time."},{"time":9270,"text":"I am also autistic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11603,"text":"People tend to diagnose autism"},{"time":13549,"text":"with really specific \ncheck-box descriptions,"},{"time":16868,"text":"but in reality, it's a whole\nvariation as to what we're like."},{"time":19916,"text":"For instance, my little brother,"},{"time":21649,"text":"he's very severely autistic."},{"time":23426,"text":"He's nonverbal. He can't talk at all."},{"time":25688,"text":"But I love to talk."},{"time":28180,"text":"People often associate autism"},{"time":31483,"text":"with liking maths and \nscience and nothing else,"},{"time":34156,"text":"but I know so many autistic people"},{"time":35955,"text":"who love being creative."},{"time":38328,"text":"But that is a stereotype,"},{"time":40770,"text":"and the stereotypes of things"},{"time":42626,"text":"are often, if not always, wrong."},{"time":45888,"text":"For instance, a lot of people"},{"time":48306,"text":"think autism and think \n\"Rain Man\" immediately."},{"time":52559,"text":"That's the common belief,"},{"time":54051,"text":"that every single autistic \nperson is Dustin Hoffman,"},{"time":57346,"text":"and that's not true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60349,"text":"But that's not just with \nautistic people, either."},{"time":63150,"text":"I've seen it with LGBTQ people,"},{"time":65490,"text":"with women, with POC people."},{"time":67910,"text":"People are so afraid of variety"},{"time":70428,"text":"that they try to fit everything \ninto a tiny little box"},{"time":73229,"text":"with really specific labels."},{"time":75524,"text":"This is something that actually"},{"time":77155,"text":"happened to me in real life:"},{"time":79833,"text":"I googled \"autistic people are ...\""},{"time":82521,"text":"and it comes up with suggestions"},{"time":84624,"text":"as to what you're going to type."},{"time":86649,"text":"I googled \"autistic people are ...\""},{"time":88404,"text":"and the top result was \"demons.\""},{"time":91617,"text":"That is the first thing that people think"},{"time":93875,"text":"when they think autism."},{"time":95879,"text":"They know."},{"time":97785,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":104604,"text":"One of the things I can do \nbecause I'm autistic —"},{"time":107201,"text":"it's an ability rather than a disability —"},{"time":109642,"text":"is I've got a very, very vivid imagination."},{"time":113177,"text":"Let me explain it to you a bit."},{"time":114850,"text":"It's like I'm walking in two \nworlds most of the time."},{"time":117100,"text":"There's the real world, \nthe world that we all share,"},{"time":119634,"text":"and there's the world in my mind,"},{"time":121614,"text":"and the world in my mind \nis often so much more real"},{"time":124651,"text":"than the real world."},{"time":127138,"text":"Like, it's very easy for \nme to let my mind loose"},{"time":130509,"text":"because I don't try and fit \nmyself into a tiny little box."},{"time":133380,"text":"That's one of the best \nthings about being autistic."},{"time":135619,"text":"You don't have the urge to do that."},{"time":137588,"text":"You find what you want to do,"},{"time":140356,"text":"you find a way to do it, \nand you get on with it."},{"time":143140,"text":"If I was trying to fit myself into a box,"},{"time":145293,"text":"I wouldn't be here, I \nwouldn't have achieved"},{"time":147445,"text":"half the things that I have now."},{"time":149595,"text":"There are problems, though."},{"time":151371,"text":"There are problems with being autistic,"},{"time":153536,"text":"and there are problems with\nhaving too much imagination."},{"time":156256,"text":"School can be a problem in general,"},{"time":158459,"text":"but having also to explain to a teacher"},{"time":162490,"text":"on a daily basis"},{"time":164672,"text":"that their lesson is inexplicably dull"},{"time":168317,"text":"and you are secretly taking refuge"},{"time":170938,"text":"in a world inside your head in \nwhich you are not in that lesson,"},{"time":174900,"text":"that adds to your list of problems."},{"time":178396,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":180264,"text":"Also, when my imagination takes hold,"},{"time":184684,"text":"my body takes on a life of its own."},{"time":186518,"text":"When something very exciting\nhappens in my inner world,"},{"time":189476,"text":"I've just got to run."},{"time":190980,"text":"I've got to rock backwards and forwards,"},{"time":192896,"text":"or sometimes scream."},{"time":194684,"text":"This gives me so much energy,"},{"time":196934,"text":"and I've got to have an \noutlet for all that energy."},{"time":199555,"text":"But I've done that ever \nsince I was a child,"},{"time":201659,"text":"ever since I was a tiny little girl."},{"time":203377,"text":"And my parents thought it was \ncute, so they didn't bring it up,"},{"time":206246,"text":"but when I got into school,"},{"time":207864,"text":"they didn't really agree that it was cute."},{"time":210165,"text":"It can be that people \ndon't want to be friends"},{"time":212830,"text":"with the girl that starts \nscreaming in an algebra lesson."},{"time":215807,"text":"And this doesn't normally \nhappen in this day and age,"},{"time":219713,"text":"but it can be that people don't want \nto be friends with the autistic girl."},{"time":223290,"text":"It can be that people \ndon't want to associate"},{"time":226572,"text":"with anyone who won't \nor can't fit themselves"},{"time":229336,"text":"into a box that's labeled normal."},{"time":232306,"text":"But that's fine with me,"},{"time":234472,"text":"because it sorts the wheat from the chaff,"},{"time":236606,"text":"and I can find which people \nare genuine and true"},{"time":239373,"text":"and I can pick these people as my friends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241929,"text":"But if you think about it, what is normal?"},{"time":245349,"text":"What does it mean?"},{"time":247160,"text":"Imagine if that was the best \ncompliment you ever received."},{"time":249940,"text":"\"Wow, you are really normal.\""},{"time":252221,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":253606,"text":"But compliments are,"},{"time":257010,"text":"\"you are extraordinary\""},{"time":258418,"text":"or \"you step outside the box.\""},{"time":260252,"text":"It's \"you're amazing.\""},{"time":261973,"text":"So if people want to be these things,"},{"time":263863,"text":"why are so many people \nstriving to be normal?"},{"time":266371,"text":"Why are people pouring their \nbrilliant individual light into a mold?"},{"time":271385,"text":"People are so afraid of variety \nthat they try and force everyone,"},{"time":276140,"text":"even people who don't want \nto or can't, to become normal."},{"time":279858,"text":"There are camps for LGBTQ people"},{"time":282697,"text":"or autistic people to try and \nmake them this \"normal,\""},{"time":286173,"text":"and that's terrifying that people \nwould do that in this day and age."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290698,"text":"All in all, I wouldn't trade my autism\nand my imagination for the world."},{"time":295305,"text":"Because I am autistic,"},{"time":297295,"text":"I've presented documentaries to the BBC,"},{"time":300287,"text":"I'm in the midst of writing a book,"},{"time":302526,"text":"I'm doing this — this is fantastic —"},{"time":304674,"text":"and one of the best \nthings that I've achieved,"},{"time":307925,"text":"that I consider to have achieved,"},{"time":310510,"text":"is I've found ways of communicating"},{"time":312492,"text":"with my little brother and sister,"},{"time":314337,"text":"who as I've said are nonverbal. \nThey can't speak."},{"time":317700,"text":"And people would often write\noff someone who's nonverbal,"},{"time":320560,"text":"but that's silly, because \nmy little brother and sister"},{"time":323294,"text":"are the best siblings that \nyou could ever hope for."},{"time":325987,"text":"They're just the best, \nand I love them so much"},{"time":328274,"text":"and I care about them \nmore than anything else."},{"time":331829,"text":"I'm going to leave you with one question:"},{"time":334507,"text":"If we can't get inside the person's minds,"},{"time":337644,"text":"no matter if they're autistic or not,"},{"time":339737,"text":"instead of punishing anything\nthat strays from normal,"},{"time":342774,"text":"why not celebrate uniqueness"},{"time":344529,"text":"and cheer every time someone\nunleashes their imagination?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":348590,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":350166,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}